"{\"uid\": \"tribuneindia.com-news-trending-can-robots-win-olympic-medals-with-hands-in-pocket-turkish-shooter-to-elon-musk-in-first-viral-post-with-8-5-million-views\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Chandigarh, August 5    Turkish shooter Yusuf Dikec---who become a global online sensation---for his causal approach and winning a Silver at the Paris Olympics has recently joined the Elon Musk-owned social media platform X, previously known as Twitter.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 253, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 24, \"end\": 31, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_language\", \"score\": 0.9933685634136858, \"rank\": 0.006541436981281391, \"text\": \"Turkish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_language\"}, {\"begin\": 40, \"end\": 45, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cat_Stevens\", \"score\": 0.9997578348057464, \"rank\": 0.00021975291647992898, \"text\": \"Yusuf\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cat_Stevens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cat_Stevens\"}, {\"begin\": 245, \"end\": 252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4224804477754094e-15, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In his first post, he dared to ask Musk if in future robots could win medals at the Olympics with their hands in their pockets?\", \"from\": 257, \"to\": 384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sharing a photo from the Olympic event, Dikec, 51, wrote, \\\"Hi Elon, do you think future robots can win medals at the Olympics with their hands in their pockets?\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 548, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How about discussing this in Istanbul, the cultural capital that unites continents?\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 578, \"end\": 586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\", \"score\": 0.9999996946460681, \"rank\": 3.030322873617377e-07, \"text\": \"Istanbul\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"@elonmusk.\\\"\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 644, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Musk responded, \\\"Robots will hit the center of the bullseye every time.\\\"\", \"from\": 645, \"to\": 717, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hi Elon, do you think future robots can win medals at the Olympics with their hands in their pockets?\\ud83d\\ude0e\\ud83c\\uddf9\\ud83c\\uddf7 How about discussing this in Istanbul, the cultural capital that unites continents?\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 907, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 856, \"end\": 864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\", \"score\": 0.9999996946460681, \"rank\": 3.030322873617377e-07, \"text\": \"Istanbul\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"@elonmuskpic.twitter.com/BR5iJmNOHD  - Yusuf Dikec (@yusufdikec)August 4, 2024      This exchange has gone insanely viral on social media and has over 8.5 million views in less than 12 hours.\", \"from\": 907, \"to\": 1098, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 949, \"end\": 954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cat_Stevens\", \"score\": 0.9997578348057464, \"rank\": 0.00021975291647992898, \"text\": \"Yusuf\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cat_Stevens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cat_Stevens\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the 51-year-old's casual attire as he fired with his other hand in pocket at the Chateauroux Shooting Centre that made him a global sensation.\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While most pistol shooters wear visors, chunky ear-defenders and shooting lenses with a blinder to shut out distractions and enhance focus, Dikec had only an yellow ear plug in as he hit the range.\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1448, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His silver hair, intense gaze, normal glasses and a jersey that looked like a regular t-shirt intrigued netizens.\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1563, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1557, \"end\": 1565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netizen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"netizens\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netizen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netizen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even the common practice among pistol shooters of firing with their non-shooting hand tucked in a pocket was seen as part of Dikec's nonchalant charm.\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1715, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dikec secured second place in the mixed team 10-metre air pistol event, along with Sevval Ilayda Tarhan.\", \"from\": 1717, \"to\": 1821, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Take your experience further with Premium access.Thought-provoking Opinions, Expert Analysis, In-depth Insights and other Member Only Benefits  Already a Member?Sign In Now  The Tribune, now published from Chandigarh, started publication on February 2, 1881, in Lahore (now in Pakistan).\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 2110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2032, \"end\": 2042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandigarh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.422847003560213e-16, \"text\": \"Chandigarh\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandigarh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandigarh\"}, {\"begin\": 2088, \"end\": 2094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lahore\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.188934718957533e-12, \"text\": \"Lahore\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lahore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lahore\"}, {\"begin\": 2103, \"end\": 2111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999729018331, \"rank\": 2.594950460478626e-08, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was started by Sardar Dyal Singh Majithia, a public-spirited philanthropist, and is run by a trust comprising five eminent persons as trustees.The Tribune, the largest selling English daily in North India, publishes news and views without any bias or prejudice of any kind.\", \"from\": 2111, \"to\": 2387, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2132, \"end\": 2138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7162354784214373e-25, \"text\": \"Sardar\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardar\"}, {\"begin\": 2139, \"end\": 2158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dyal_Singh_Majithia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dyal Singh Majithia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dyal_Singh_Majithia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dyal_Singh_Majithia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Restraint and moderation, rather than agitational language and partisanship, are the hallmarks of the newspaper.\", \"from\": 2388, \"to\": 2500, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is an independent newspaper in the real sense of the term.The Tribune has two sister publications, Punjabi Tribune (in Punjabi) and Dainik Tribune (in Hindi).\", \"from\": 2501, \"to\": 2662, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2606, \"end\": 2621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_Tribune\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Punjabi Tribune\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_Tribune\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_Tribune\"}, {\"begin\": 2626, \"end\": 2633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_language\", \"score\": 0.9998836623844587, \"rank\": 0.00011517841353388244, \"text\": \"Punjabi\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2639, \"end\": 2653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dainik_Tribune\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dainik Tribune\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dainik_Tribune\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dainik_Tribune\"}, {\"begin\": 2658, \"end\": 2663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hindi\", \"score\": 0.9999830936079764, \"rank\": 1.651186640233034e-05, \"text\": \"Hindi\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hindi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hindi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Remembering Sardar Dyal Singh Majithia\", \"from\": 2664, \"to\": 2702, \"entities\": []}]}"